  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-04 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level is 3. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are fully assessed; one factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' on the grounds that the assessment team judged it inapplicable to a purely computational COU with no physical test article. The rationale argues the factor does not apply, yet the encoding uses 'not-assessed' rather than 'not-applicable', silently leaving a material credibility gap at MRL 3. All other factors show achieved levels at or above required levels, supporting an Accepted outcome that obscures the unaddressed gap.",
