      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for velocity and hemolysis index QoIs; GCI < 5% on fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 3.1% for area-averaged hemolysis index and 2.8% for peak wall shear stress on the fine mesh (8.4 M cells). Discretization error is within the 5% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented and traceable to calibrated instruments.",
      "rationale": "All five operating points replicate FDA benchmark conditions. Flow rates set by Coriolis meter (±0.5%), rotational speed by optical tachometer (±2 RPM), temperature controlled at 37 ± 0.5 °C. Hematocrit fixed at 40 ± 1%. Achieved level exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or NRMSE) computed for hemolysis index and velocity profiles; statistical validation metric reported.",
      "rationale": "Normalised RMSE for PIV velocity profiles is 4.7%; hemolysis index predictions agree with bench measurements within 12% across all five operating points. Validation metric U_val computed per ASME V&V 20 and reported in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, velocity profiles) are the same as or directly predictive of the COU decision QoI (absolute hemolysis index).",
      "rationale": "The primary validation QoI — modified index of hemolysis (MIH) — is identical to the regulatory decision QoI. Velocity field comparison provides additional mechanistic confidence. Relevance is high; achieved level exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under operating conditions overlapping the VAD COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities use the exact FDA generic pump geometry. Operating conditions span 2.5–6 L/min at 2500–3500 RPM, fully enclosing the VAD COU envelope of 3–5 L/min at 3000 RPM. Relevance to the COU is confirmed at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals reduced by at least four orders of magnitude; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residual levels below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; hemolysis scalar residual below 1e-5. Mass imbalance is 0.003%. Solver error is controlled at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed boundary condition assignments, turbulence model settings, and hemolysis model constants against the documented simulation plan. No discrepancies were found. Use error controls are adequate at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selected based on documented literature review; sensitivity to model form alternatives reported.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published FDA pump benchmark studies. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) used with constants calibrated to Heun et al. Sensitivity study comparing RNG k-epsilon shows < 8% difference in MIH. Model form adequacy confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in key model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants) quantified; Monte Carlo propagation performed; 95th-percentile hemolysis prediction reported.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo analysis (n=2000) propagates uncertainty in blood viscosity (CV 8%), density (CV 0.5%), and hemolysis model exponents (CV 15%). The 95th-percentile MIH prediction remains below the clinical threshold of 0.8 g/dL. Input uncertainty is fully characterised."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood analogue fluid characterised; rheological properties measured and reported; sample lot traceability documented.",
      "rationale": "Glycerol-water analogue (40% glycerol by mass) used in PIV experiments; viscosity and density measured at 37 °C and documented. Hemolysis bench tests used porcine blood with hematocrit 40 ± 1%; lot numbers and storage conditions recorded. Test sample characterisation meets requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrate that input parameters used in validation experiments (fluid properties, geometry tolerances, operating conditions) are equivalent to those in the COU device and operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that this factor does not apply to the present COU because the COU is entirely computational and no physical device prototype was available for comparison. No parametric equivalency mapping between the validation test article and the intended VAD device was performed. The factor was therefore left not-assessed rather than formally scoped out, on the informal judgment that the FDA generic pump geometry is sufficiently representative. This reasoning does not satisfy the 'not-applicable' criterion under ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1, which requires documented justification and stakeholder agreement; however, the status 'not-assessed' was assigned without escalation."
    }
  ],
