    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors were assessed and all achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at Model Risk Level 3. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms the 95th-percentile hemolysis prediction remains below the clinical threshold. The team accepted the package on the basis of the twelve assessed factors, treating the unassessed Equivalency of input parameters factor as non-material on the informal grounds that the validation geometry matches the COU geometry. No formal not-applicable determination was documented for that factor.",
